    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PDCP initialization inconsistency in LTE UE softmodem\n\n### Summary\nThe LTE UE softmodem had inconsistent logic between UE ID calculation and PDCP initialization, causing unexpected behavior when node-number parameter was used. The ue_id_g variable was calculated using one formula while init_pdcp() was called with a different UE ID, leading to mismatches in PDCP context initialization.\n\nThis inconsistency caused issues when running multiple UEs or when node-number was set to values other than the default. In some cases, negative UE IDs were being passed to PDCP initialization, causing undefined behavior.\n\nThe fix ensures that init_pdcp() is called with the same UE ID that is used for other UE-related functions, making the behavior consistent and predictable.\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/lte-uesoftmodem.c`: Made init_pdcp() call use the same UE ID as ue_id_g calculation\n- `executables/lte-uesoftmodem.c`: Added validation to prevent negative UE IDs from being passed to PDCP initialization\n"
}